媒体指责总统团队发出了一系列虚假的声明，对媒体进行攻击。<ref>{{cite news|date=2017-01-23|title=从观礼人数到现场天气，白宫的话有几分真相？|url=http://cn.nytstyle.com/international/20170123/president-trump-inauguration-crowd-white-house/|newspaper=纽约时报|accessdate=2017-01-25|archive-date=2017-02-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170219052451/http://cn.nytstyle.com/international/20170123/president-trump-inauguration-crowd-white-house/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vanityfair.com/news/2017/01/sean-spicer-inauguration-statement-lies |title=Trump Spokesman Sean Spicer's Lecture on Media Accuracy Is Peppered With Lies |work=Vanity Fair |date=2014-01-02 |accessdate=2017-01-22 |archive-date=2017-01-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122055956/http://www.vanityfair.com/news/2017/01/sean-spicer-inauguration-statement-lies |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Nick Baumann Senior Enterprise Editor, The Huffington Post |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/trump-lies-crowd-size_us_5884104ae4b0e3a735699697 |title=Trump And His Press Secretary Flagrantly Lied on Their First Full Day in Office. That Matters. |work=[[赫芬顿邮报|赫芬顿邮报]] |date=2017-01-21 |accessdate=2017-01-22 |archive-date=2019-02-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190213223320/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/trump-lies-crowd-size_us_5884104ae4b0e3a735699697 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Kessler |first=Glenn |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/fact-checker/wp/2017/01/22/spicer-earns-four-pinocchios-for-a-series-of-false-claims-on-inauguration-crowd-size |title=Spicer earns Four Pinocchios for false claims on inauguration crowd size |work=华盛顿邮报 |accessdate=2017-01-22 |archive-date=2017-01-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122194054/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/fact-checker/wp/2017/01/22/spicer-earns-four-pinocchios-for-a-series-of-false-claims-on-inauguration-crowd-size/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>媒体并称新总统上任仅三天，因为人群规模的“另类事实”，特朗普在记者提问下拒绝公布报税单并称“只有记者在乎，人民不在乎”，以及虽然没有证据但与国会议员谈话时声称有3-5百万非法移民在大选中为民主党投票等一系列媒体负面报道，特朗普已与媒体处于“战争状态”。

